{"000-section": {"000-title": "AP YSR Arogya Asara Scheme \u2013 Relief to Poor Patients Post Hospitalization"}, "001-section": {"000-title": "Andhra Pradesh govt. AP YSR Arogya Asara Scheme 2019 to provide Rs. 5,000 p.m (Rs. 225 / day) relief to patients after discharge from hospitals"}, "002-section": {"000-title": "AP YSR Arogya Aasara Scheme 2019", "001-normal": "As a part of AP govt\u2019s flagship [YSR Arogyari Scheme](https://sarkariyojana.com/ap-dr-ysr-aarogyasri-scheme-health-card/), the state govt. has launched AP YSR Arogya Asara Scheme. The state govt. will provide Rs. 225 / day or Rs. 5,000 / month to patients for the prescribed relaxation time after discharge from hospitals. At Guntur government hospital, CM has distributed cheques to YSR Arogya Aasara Scheme beneficiaries who had just received treatment.", "002-normal": "Though the AP YSR Arogya Asara Scheme has come into effect from 1 December 2019, it is formally launched on 2 Nov 2019. All the accounts of patients are credited with money in 48-hour period of discharge from the hospital. AP govt. has issued guidelines for usage of 836 types of surgeries in 26 separate departments.", "003-normal": "All the beneficiary patients must provide bank account and Aadhaar card details at the time of discharge. In case a bank account is not provided, then the money would be credited into their relative\u2019s bank account. The authorities have already completed all arrangements in the wake of the Chief Minister\u2019s directive to ensure there are no hurdles.", "004-normal": "\u0c30\u0c3e\u0c37\u0c4d\u0c1f\u0c4d\u0c30\u0c02\u0c32\u0c4b \u0c2e\u0c02\u0c1a\u0c3f \u0c2a\u0c3e\u0c32\u0c28 \u0c38\u0c3e\u0c17\u0c41\u0c24\u0c41\u0c02\u0c1f\u0c47 \u0c1c\u0c40\u0c30\u0c4d\u0c23\u0c3f\u0c02\u0c1a\u0c41\u0c15\u0c4b\u0c32\u0c47\u0c15 \u0c28\u0c3e \u0c2e\u0c24\u0c02, \u0c15\u0c41\u0c32\u0c02 \u0c17\u0c41\u0c30\u0c3f\u0c02\u0c1a\u0c3f \u0c2e\u0c3e\u0c1f\u0c4d\u0c32\u0c3e\u0c21\u0c41\u0c24\u0c41\u0c28\u0c4d\u0c28\u0c3e\u0c3